1:Information:Information about this tool:info
2:Settings   :Change various system settings:
2.1:System       :e.g. Resize SD, Overclocking, Hostname:
2.1.1:Resize SD   :Expand root partition to fill SD card:resizesd
2.1.2:Overclocking:Configure overclocking:overclocking
2.1.3:Hostname    :Change the default hostname:xbhostname
2.1.4:Timezone    :Set the default timezone:timezone
2.1.5:Kernel      :Switches the kernel:switchkernel
2.2:User Accounts:e.g. Change passwords:
2.2.1:XBian Password:Change password for xbian user:xbianpass
2.2.2:Root Password :Change password for root user:rootpass
2.3:Networking   :e.g. LAN/WLAN Settings, SSH:
2.3.1:WLAN          :Configure wireless network connection:wlan
2.3.2:LAN           :Configure wired network connection:lan
2.3.3:SSH root login:Enable/Disable SSH root login:sshroot
2.4:Connectivity :e.g. Video-output:
2.4.1:Video Output:Change HDMI, CEC and overscan behavior:videoflags
2.5:Licenses     :Add/Remove hardware decoding licenses:
2.5.1:VC1  :Enter/remove your VC1 license:licensevc1
2.5.2:MPG2 :Enter/remove your MPG2 license:licensempg2
2.6:Programs     :Start/Stop services etc.:servicemanager
3:Packages   :Install or remove additional packages:
3.1:Remote:Install packages from internet:remotepackages
3.2:Local :Install packages from *.tar.gz:localpackages
4:Updates    :Check for XBian updates:notimplemented
